{"session_id": "442f141c-908d-431c-b446-8675c95fdcc8", "task": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze this conversation to create a comprehensive summary.\n\n1. **Initial Project Review**: User asked to read README.md. ClawCorp is a \"Self-Evolving AI Organization\" - virtual software & research org with dynamic HR, file-based state, scientific method approach.\n\n2. **Stack Discussion**: Long brainstorming about tech stack choices:\n   - Started with Next.js (already set up)\n   - Discussed Go, Rust, Bun+Hono, TypeScript options\n   - User pushed back on Go saying TypeScript is better for AI tools\n   - User asked if Next.js is a good choice - concluded it's not ideal for persistent processes/WebSockets\n   - User said \"Bun+Hono has not big difference between Next.js\" - acknowledged stateless vs persistent server is the key difference\n   - Final decision: **Bun + Hono + React + Vite**\n\n3. **Rebuild**: User said \"delete all my code, let's rebuild!\" - wiped Next.js, kept agents/ and README.md, built new structure with server/ (Bun+Hono) and client/ (React+Vite)\n\n4. **Git Issues**: Fixed .gitignore - was only ignoring root /node_modules, not subdirectories. Fixed to use `node_modules/` recursively.\n\n5. **MVP Build**: Built minimum viable version:\n   - AgentRunner.ts - spawns processes, streams stdout/stderr\n   - WebSocket hub for broadcasting\n   - Run/kill routes\n   - Basic Kanban UI with live log panel\n\n6. **Port conflict**: Server couldn't start - port 3001 in use from testing. Fixed with `lsof -ti:3001 | xargs kill -9`\n\n7. **OpenCode issues**: \n   - research-assistant had `type: \"code\"` with python3 -c which ran prompt as Python code \u2192 SyntaxError\n   - User said \"\u6211\u4eec\u5148\u7528opencode!\" - switch to opencode\n   - Discovered opencode syntax: `opencode run [message]` not